{
  "text": "In the case gas derives from bacteria, the theory of counterperfusion-supersaturation has been postulated, and it sustains that the production of nitrogen by intraluminal bacteria overflows the plasma concentration producing a plasma-intraluminal gradient and causing a diffusion of nitrogen into submucosal vessels which would explain the gas pattern found through the blood vessels in the border of the mesentery [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "573582"
